9:
Yes. I've got a longer vacation
coming up, so I was thinking of
heading back home.
11:
I was wondering if there were any
nice souvenirs I could take with me.
15:
I see. But, specialties? That might
prove... difficult.
20:
I heard there was nothing to be
found around here until Palpebra
was established.
24:
If Palpebra's known for anything, it's
the Kaleidoscope, but... It's not like
you could take that home with you...
28:
Then maybe I could just take a rock
from the Kaleidoscope?
31: Would that really be a souvenir?
34:
W-well... We'll be back in Palpebra
soon, so let's take a little look around
when get there.
40:
All right! I'm not going back for a
while, so we can take our time—
44:
Dammit, not here! This... This can't
be how it ends!
56:
Th-thank you... for your help... I
promise to... return the favor...
someday...
59:
W-wait! Your wounds look serious. It
would be a fatal mistake to push
yourself any further.
61:
Fortunately, we aren't far from
Palpebra. We'll take you to a doctor—
64:
Y-you can't! I have to get this
medicine to the village as soon as I
can!
74:
...I understand. Please tell me how to
get to your village.
90:
I imagine you'll need help with the
local terrain. Allow me to be your
navigator.
95:
Then we'll take this person to the
doctor.
101: Special Week. We're counting on you!
111: Light! Should I go this way?
123: Don't worry! Compared to a race...
131:
Light! I'm going to keep speeding up,
so hang on tight!
138: We'll make it in time, no matter what!
150:
Hey! Glad to see you both safe and
sound.
153: Did you deliver the medicine on time?
164:
That man is going to be all right, too.
He got checked out at the hospital
and they said he'll be recovering
there for a little while.
168:
That's a relief. We'll have to go
inform him of the situation later.
173:
Yes! I'm sure he's feeling very
anxious.
178:
Thank you very much for your help.
Without you, we may have been
forced to choose who to save.
182:
N-no, not at all! I just knew what I
had to do...
185: Um... Actually, I have two moms.
188:
There's Mom, who raised me and
sent me to Tracen Academy...
191:
And Mama, who passed away when
I was born.
195: I love them both very much...
199:
So when I heard about that man's
situation, I knew I had to do
whatever I could to help him.
204: ...I see. I'm really glad you were there.
213:
Now then, we'll need to prepare
some very special souvenirs for you
to bring back home.
218:
After we deliver the news about the
medicine, let's go look around for
something nice!
224: We'll show you all the best shops.
